results.name: Numbers that are not the sum of 4 nonnegative cubes.
comment: Conjecture: The sequence is finite, with 113936676 terms, the largest being 7373170279850 (cf. Deshouillers et al, 2000, Conj. 1 and 2). (End)
link: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n=1..10000
Jean-Marc Deshouillers, Francois Hennecart and Bernard Landreau; appendix by I. Gusti Putu Purnaba, 7373170279850, Math. Comp., Vol. 69, No. 229 (2000), 421-439.
Index entries for sequences related to sums of cubes
program: (PARI) cubes(bound) = my(v=[], x=0); while(1, v=concat(v, [x^3]); x++; if(x^3 > bound, return(v)))
a025448(n) = my(i=0, c=cubes(n)); for(s=1, #c, for(t=s, #c, for(u=t, #c, for(v=u, #c, if(n==c[s]+c[t]+c[u]+c[v], i++))))); i
